  "prompt": "Which are the best stem cell research labs in India for doing masters dissertion project on stem cell?",
  "response": "While there are several institutes and research facilities in India renowned for their work in stem cell research, the following are some of the most prominent ones where you might consider pursuing a master's dissertation project:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Science (IISc), Bangalore**: The IISc is known for its cutting-edge research in various fields, including stem cell biology. The various departments may offer opportunities for master's projects.\n\n2. **National Centre for Biological Sciences (NCBS), Bangalore**: NCBS is involved in groundbreaking research in molecular biology, including stem cell research. They have a strong focus on developmental biology and genetics.\n\n3. **Institute for Stem Cell Science and Regenerative Medicine (inStem), Bangalore**: This institute is dedicated to developing basic and applied science in stem cell research and is affiliated with NCBS. They offer opportunities for students to work on various stem cell projects.\n\n4. **All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), New Delhi**: AIIMS is a leading medical research institute in India, and its research on stem cells spans many disciplines, including regenerative medicine and oncology.\n\n5. **Tata Memorial Centre (TMC), Mumbai**: TMC is one of the premier cancer research institutes in India and is involved in innovative research using stem cells for cancer treatment.\n\n6. **M.S. Ramaiah Medical College, Bangalore**: This college has a dedicated stem cell research unit and offers opportunities for students to work on various aspects of stem cell biology.\n\n7. **Dhirubhai Ambani Institute of Information and Communication Technology (DAIICT), Gandhinagar**: DAIICT is involved in interdisciplinary research, including bioinformatics and genomics, which can complement a stem cell research project.\n\n8. **Bharathiar University, Coimbatore**: The university has ongoing research in stem cell biology and may provide opportunities for master's students.\n\n9. **University of Hyderabad**: The university has strong programs in life sciences and is involved in stem cell research.\n\n10. **Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU), New Delhi**: The School of Life Sciences at JNU conducts innovative research in various areas, including stem cell research.\n\nWhen selecting a lab or institute, consider contacting potential supervisors to discuss your research interests, funding opportunities, and the specifics of ongoing projects. Be sure to review their faculty bios and recent publications to find a match for your interests.",
